#: ../../../release_details/9.5/fix-polygon-centroid.md:1
msgid "Polygon centroid computation fixed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/fix-polygon-centroid.md:3
msgid "An issue with `vtkPolygon::ComputeCentroid()` has been fixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/fix-polygon-centroid.md:5
msgid ""
"Instead of projecting polygon points to the x-y or x-z plane, compute the "
"center and then use a composite weighted-area triangulation to estimate the "
"centroid. This is robust to non-planar polygons. The projection method would "
"assume an x-y projection was acceptable with even minor perturbations from "
"planarity for x-z polygons. This in turn would lead to a centroid placed on "
"an edge of the polygon rather than near its center, causing other tests "
"(such as `vtkPolyhedron::IsConvex()`) to fail seemingly at random."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/fix-polygon-centroid.md:15
msgid ""
"This also adds a planarity tolerance to the computation of the centroid. If "
"the polygon is significantly non-planar, the centroid computation will fail."
msgstr ""
